The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Thursday, July 28, 2005 

 IN THE CITY

 Calcutta: The Kaviguru Rally, organised by Bengal Motor Sports Club, will be run in single leg from Calcutta to Shantiniketan on Saturday. A total of 30 two wheelers and 20 four wheelers will take part.

 Pailan Group will be the sponsors in association with The Telegraph and Exide. The total distance is 272.64 km and the total driving time will be approximately seven hours.

 The vehicles will be flagged off from the Pailan campus. The rally will be run with the status of a national event under the FMSCI guidelines with 25 per cent of the route comprising unsealed surfaces.

 The speed to be attained by the vehicles will be between 40 and 70 km per hour in dirt sections and forest tracks.

 The total prize money will be Rs 1 lakh.

 GENERAL: Special Olympics at Salt Lake Stadium from 5 pm.




